user_location: of Red Cow (Minneapolis - Fulton) Minneapolis, Alabama
review_blob: 1L btl. Thanks James Birnie! Episode IV (2012). Nose is vanilla, oak, alcohol, liquorice. Black, slight tan head, quickly evaporated, but heavy legs left. Taste is vanilla and oak, slight boozy warmth, doesnt burn, great balance. Palate is silky, slightly oily but not unpleasant. Whoa! So complex! Give this to a wine snob or whiskey brat and theyd be hooked. This is the most wood and vanilla Ive ever had with a beer, after 2 yrs I think the cocoa died a bit but its there in the finish. Top 5 Ive had maybe #2

user_location: of Red Cow (Minneapolis - Fulton) Minneapolis, Alabama
review_blob: On draft at brewery. 11/2/13. Aroma is chocolate, hazelnut, vanilla. Appearance is jet black, tan head, very little, almost no lacing. Chocolate is present but not dominant, slight sweetness from lactose. Hits palate nicely, balanced flavors. Velvety without being thick. Overall very nicely done. Top 5 chocolate stout. Now make more of it so I can get a growler.

user_location: of Red Cow (Minneapolis - Fulton) Minneapolis, Alabama
review_blob: Bottle. Aroma is burnt carmel, honey and mild hop. Copper-reddish with off white head, some lacing. Super malty, overwhelms hop characteristics. Sweet and a little oak? Heavy booze with a slight hop bittering. Should not be classified as IPA, too sweet and malty. Closer to barley wine with how much malt I get. Very disappointed

review_blob: Taproom 8/3/13. 5% 75 IBU. Aroma of resinous piney hops. Cooper hazy with white head and good lacing. Taste is hop forward, piney resin, grain malt that has a tart finish which is not good but is still tasty. Surly Furious fans will fig this hoppy version of a cali common. Delicious overall

review_blob:
Taproom. 8/3/13 6.6% and 29 IBU 
10oz tulip. Very little dark tan head with almost no lacing. Local, good quality coffee aroma with a slight chocolate sweetness. Taste very much like the smell, coffee dominant along with nice roasted malt backbone, slightly sweet. Light bodied for the style but still substantial, balanced and lingering. Overall a solid coffee porter but not top 5 by any stretch.
